                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.773/38.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Guthrie</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 234, March 8. Consul, Dairen, telegraphs discrimination against American
                    vessels still exists. Request Foreign Office to instruct railway authorities to
                    grant the reduced rates to shipments in other than Japanese vessels whether to
                    Newchwang or Dairen as necessary to preserve open door.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
